Core Idea (Agentic System View)

TalentMatch shouldn’t be just a tool—it should behave like a team of AI agents:

🤖 Recruiter Agent
🤖 Resume Analyst Agent
🤖 Candidate Engagement Agent
🤖 Interview Coordinator Agent
🤖 Hiring Decision Assistant

Each agent has clear responsibilities + tools + memory + goals

🧩 2. Core Components You Should Build
1. 📄 Resume Ingestion & Understanding Engine

Use case: Upload + parse resumes intelligently

Features:
PDF/DOC upload
Resume parsing (skills, experience, education)
Store:
Structured data → PostgreSQL
Embeddings → Vector DB (Chroma / Pinecone)
Resume classification:
Role (Backend / Data / DevOps)
Seniority (Junior/Mid/Senior)
Agent:

👉 Resume Analyzer Agent

Extracts meaning, not just keywords
Normalizes skills (e.g., “Spring Boot” = “Java Backend”)
2. 🔍 Semantic Candidate Search (RAG-based)

Use case: “Find me Java dev with AWS + 5 yrs exp”

Features:
Natural language query → embedding
Vector similarity search
Filters:
Experience
Location
Skills
Ranking score
Agent:

👉 Talent Search Agent

Combines:
Semantic search (vector DB)
Structured filters (PostgreSQL)
3. 🧠 JD (Job Description) Intelligence Engine

Use case: Upload JD → system understands requirements

Features:
Extract:
Required skills
Optional skills
Experience range
Generate:
Ideal candidate profile
Matching criteria
Agent:

👉 JD Analyzer Agent

Converts JD → structured + embedding
4. 🎯 Candidate Matching & Scoring Engine

Use case: Rank candidates for a JD

Features:
Matching score:
Skill match %
Experience relevance
Semantic similarity
Explainability:
“Why this candidate is a good fit”
Agent:

👉 Matching Agent

Combines:
Resume embedding
JD embedding
Business rules
5. 💬 Candidate Engagement Agent (Chatbot)

Use case: Talk to candidates automatically

Features:
Ask screening questions
Collect missing info
Answer candidate queries
Personalized responses
Channels:
WhatsApp / Email / Web chat
Agent:

👉 Conversational Recruiting Agent

Maintains candidate context (memory)
6. 📅 Interview Scheduling Agent

Use case: Automate interview coordination

Features:
Check interviewer availability
Suggest time slots
Send invites
Reschedule automatically
Agent:

👉 Scheduler Agent

Integrates with:
Google Calendar / Outlook
7. 🧪 Screening & Evaluation Engine

Use case: Pre-screen candidates before interview

Features:
AI-generated screening questions
Coding/MCQ tests
Resume-based questions
Agent:

👉 Screening Agent

Adaptive questioning based on candidate profile
8. 📊 Hiring Insights & Analytics Dashboard

Use case: Help HR make decisions

Features:
Funnel metrics:
Applied → Shortlisted → Interviewed → Selected
Skill demand trends
Hiring time analytics
9. 🧠 Hiring Decision Assistant (AI Copilot)

Use case: Help recruiter decide

Features:
Compare candidates
Summarize strengths/weaknesses
Predict success probability
Agent:

👉 Decision Agent

Gives:
“Top 3 candidates for this role”
“Risk factors”
10. 🗂️ Candidate Memory & Profile Timeline

Use case: Long-term candidate tracking

Features:
Interaction history
Previous interviews
Feedback logs
Concept:

👉 This is your agent memory layer